<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Last year we <a href="http://blog.springsource.com/2010/11/15/yet-another-flavour-of-gorm-mongodb/#comments">introduced support for MongoDB in GORM</a> (along with many <a href="http://blog.springsource.com/2010/09/07/announcing-gorm-for-redis/">other</a> <a href="http://grails.1312388.n4.nabble.com/ANN-GORM-for-Riak-td3090059.html">GORM</a> <a href="http://blog.springsource.com/2010/10/26/introducing-gorm-for-gemfire/">implementations</a>) and it has been extremely well received by the community. We have had a ton of feedback, and today we are pleased to announce a new release (Milestone 2) which addresses some of the feedback we have received.</p>
<p><strong>Embedded Document Support</strong></p>
<p>The number one requested feature was nested document support and in this release we have improved that significantly. Now you can embed other domains using the standard embedded mapping in GORM:</p>
